      "role": "user",
      "content": "that makes sense. but when u say \"effectiveness depends on implementation\", isnt it pretty much settled in most academic studies that these laws end up hurting marginalized people more than they actually stop crime? like, is there even a real scientific basis for the deterrence argument anymore or is it just a political talking point at this point?",
